The paper presents a large-scale graph embedding system that can handle graphs with billions of nodes and trillions of edges. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of graph partitioning and parallelization, which are common techniques in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper evaluates the system on social network graphs and the Freebase dataset, which are commonly used in Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) research.
